Disney said on Thursday it was working on 10 “Star Wars” series for Disney+, along with more than a dozen shows from Pixar and Marvel. The company also said 15 movies, including “Pinocchio” and “Peter Pan & Wendy,” will release directly on Disney+.

Congressional Democrats are pushing President-elect Joe Biden to cancel as much as $50,000 per person in student debt, quickly and by executive action. He wants $10,000 per person by legislation, however, setting up a clash with his own party.
